            "id": "8ad1e62d-5d6d-4072-a1ee-25a2df0e823d",
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The terminal message or code output you provided is a YAML configuration snippet from a Spring Boot application. Let's break down each part of the YAML configuration and the error message:\n\n### YAML Configuration Breakdown\n\n1. **JWT Configuration:**\n   ```yaml\n   jwt:\n     secret: ${JWT_SECRET:default_local_secret}\n     expiration: 86400000\n   ```\n   - **`secret`:** This is a placeholder for the JWT secret key. It uses environment variable substitution, where `${JWT_SECRET}` is the environment variable. If `JWT_SECRET` is not set, it defaults to `default_local_secret`.\n   - **`expiration`:** This sets the expiration time for the JWT tokens in milliseconds. `86400000` milliseconds equals 24 hours.\n\n2. **Spring Data MongoDB Configuration:**\n   ```yaml\n   spring:\n     data:\n       mongodb:\n         uri: mongodb://localhost:27017/assessment_db\n         database: assessment_db\n         auto-index-creation: true\n   ```\n   - **`uri`:** Specifies the MongoDB connection URI. It connects to a MongoDB instance running on `localhost` at port `27017` and uses the `assessment_db` database.\n   - **`database`:** Specifies the name of the database to use, which is `assessment_db`.\n   - **`auto-index-creation`:** When set to `true`, it enables automatic creation of indexes for MongoDB collections.\n\n3. **Logging Configuration:**\n   ```yaml\n   logging:\n     level:\n       org.springframework.security: DEBUG\n       org.springframework.data.mongodb: DEBUGauto-index-creation: false\n   ```\n   - **`org.springframework.security: DEBUG`:** Sets the logging level for Spring Security to `DEBUG`, which provides detailed logging information useful for debugging.\n   - **`org.springframework.data.mongodb: DEBUGauto-index-creation: false`:** This line contains an error. It attempts to set the logging level for `org.springframework.data.mongodb` to `DEBUG` and also includes `auto-index-creation: false` on the same line, which is incorrect YAML syntax.\n\n### Error Explanation\n\n- **Error Message:**\n  ```\n  It is forbidden to specify block composed value at the same line as key\n  ```\n  This error indicates that the YAML syntax is incorrect because a block composed value (in this case, `auto-index-creation: false`) is specified on the same line as a key (`org.springframework.data.mongodb: DEBUG`). In YAML, each key-value pair should be on its own line unless using inline syntax, which is not the case here.\n\n### Resolution\n\nTo resolve the error, you should separate the logging configuration into distinct lines for clarity and correctness:\n\n```yaml\nlogging:\n  level:\n    org.springframework.security: DEBUG\n    org.springframework.data.mongodb: DEBUG\n  auto-index-creation: false\n```\n\nThis change ensures that each configuration setting is properly formatted and avoids YAML syntax errors."
